The percentage total return refers to how much of the initial investment is given off as a return. To do this, we first need to solve for the total gain of this share by adding together the dividends earned and the difference in price of the stocks.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total percentage gain}&=\dfrac{\text{dividends}+(\text{initial price}-\text{final price})}{\text{initial price}}
\end{aligned}$$
